sb|W|NT||cp|8|AT|^B@2^Y@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Basically, the 2NT bid (Ogust) asks the opener 2 questions:
a) How good is your suit?
b) How good is your hand?|
PG| ***** 29 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|^B@2^Y@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|A good suit is defined as having 2 of the top 3 honors. A good hand is defined as having 8+ HCP. So, the 4 combinations of good/bad suit and hand can be described using the 4 bids between 3C and 3S. All responses to Ogust are artificial. If Moe bids 3C, that shows a bad hand (7 HCP or less) and a bad suit (not 2 of top 3) which is the worst hand he can have. 3S, which Moe just bid, shows the best hand he can have. Good suit (2 of top 3) and good hand (8+). Then, 3D would show a bad hand (7 or less) and a good suit and 3H would show a good hand (8 or more) and a bad suit.|
